Olive Oil
2 potato
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Slow-Cooked Beef Brisket
1 sachet Gravy Granules
½ cup boiling water
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 bag Brussels sprouts
1 packet Worcestershire sauce

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place potato on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle with garlic & herb seasoning, drizzle with
olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
• Meanwhile, place slow-cooked beef brisket in a baking dish. Pour liquid from the packaging over beef.
• Cover tightly with foil and bake for 12 minutes. Turn beef, then re-cover with foil and bake until heated through and liquid has slightly reduced, a further 12 minutes.

• Meanwhile, halve Brussels sprouts. When potatoes have 15 minutes remaining, add Brussels sprouts to one side of the tray with a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt. Roast until the veggies are tender, 15 minutes.
• While the veggies are roasting, boil the kettle.
• In a medium heatproof bowl, combine gravy granules, Worcestershire sauce and the boiling water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people), whisking, until smooth, 1 minute. Set aside.
• Add baby spinach leaves to a medium microwave-safe bowl, then cover with a damp paper towel.
• Microwave spinach on high in 20 second bursts, until just wilted.
• Add roasted Brussels sprouts to the bowl of spinach, then toss to combine.

• Slice beef brisket.
• Divide greens, herbed potatoes and brisket between plates.
• Pour Worcestershire gravy over beef to serve. Enjoy